timeline.bodyText:
I would put the none-condition first like it is defined in WorkflowConditionType for consistency. Also, it might be the most likely case anyway. We wouldn't have to evaluate all options all the time.
Might make sense to change the if/else if block to a switch-statement now though.
switch (type.toLowerCase()) {
    case "none": { … }
    case "script": { … }
    case "xpath": { … }
    default: { Exception }
}

